373
00:22:43.322 --> 00:22:46.682
at baseline as well is able to induce neuroendocrine

374
00:22:46.722 --> 00:22:49.822
markers. But this is enriched when FOX2B is

375
00:22:49.882 --> 00:22:51.322
overexpressed.

376
00:22:52.802 --> 00:22:53.762
Next, we

377
00:22:55.102 --> 00:22:57.762
did single-cell RNA seq analysis on our

378
00:22:59.122 --> 00:23:02.822
in vitro models of EGFR mutant LUADs with or

379
00:23:02.862 --> 00:23:06.642
without FOX2B overexpression, and Mamie did the single-cell RNA seq analysis, and

380
00:23:06.702 --> 00:23:10.222
here showing across the UMAP that the clusters that were

381
00:23:10.282 --> 00:23:14.242
highest on FOX2B show clearly lower levels

382
00:23:14.422 --> 00:23:18.382
of EGFR signaling. And usually when we overexpress FOX2B,

383
00:23:18.502 --> 00:23:22.422
we see the cells being very stressed, which makes sense since they are

384
00:23:22.442 --> 00:23:25.742
having a reduction in their main oncogenetic drive.

385
00:23:27.442 --> 00:23:31.282
We also-- Oh, sorry. Yeah. We also proceeded to do

386
00:23:31.322 --> 00:23:34.882
FOX2B ChIP-seq, and we were able to see nice binding of

387
00:23:34.982 --> 00:23:38.802
FOX2B at the EGFR locus, in the promoter, and

388
00:23:38.842 --> 00:23:42.622
throughout the gene body. So it is likely that FOX2B is

389
00:23:42.642 --> 00:23:46.602
preventing EGFR transcription, and that's how it's

390
00:23:46.642 --> 00:23:49.362
leading to lower levels of EGFR signal.

391
00:23:51.242 --> 00:23:55.012
Also wanted to point out that FOX2B induction of neuroendocrine

392
00:23:55.062 --> 00:23:57.142
markers is not unique to

393
00:23:58.482 --> 00:24:02.282
EGFR mutant lung adenocarcinoma only, but we are also able to

394
00:24:02.342 --> 00:24:04.602
observe it in other LUAD-driven contexts.

395
00:24:06.002 --> 00:24:09.862
So when we overexpressed FOX2B in two KRAS-driven cell lines,

396
00:24:09.962 --> 00:24:12.702
we were able to see induction of different neuroendocrine

397
00:24:12.722 --> 00:24:15.938
markers.As well as also in

398
00:24:16.018 --> 00:24:19.647
ALK-driven LUAD in one cell line, we were able to see

399
00:24:19.698 --> 00:24:23.478
induction of neuroendocrine markers and a decrease in total ALK.

400
00:24:27.428 --> 00:24:31.358
When I was practicing, I didn't go through the slide as quickly as now, but

401
00:24:32.138 --> 00:24:35.838
yeah. So I had removed a lot of things actually, so maybe the discussion would be a

402
00:24:35.898 --> 00:24:38.678
bit longer. But yeah, this brings me to future directions.

403
00:24:38.778 --> 00:24:42.758
So we are currently working on validating the mechanism by which

404
00:24:42.818 --> 00:24:44.898
FOX2B induces neuroendocrine markers,

405
00:24:45.838 --> 00:24:49.598
and also, we're working on knocking out FOX2B in transformed

406
00:24:49.698 --> 00:24:52.778
small cell line. So we did knock out FOX2B in...

